<td width='100%' class='newssubject' colspan='2'><a name='news_'></a>Everquest finally gets Instant Msging<br>
<font class='smallcomments'>[ <a href='/forums/showthread.php?threadid=7306' class='smallcommentshi'>12 comments</a> ] submitted by: Goadan</font><br>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width='15'>&nbsp;</td>
<td>
<br>*from Casters Realm*<br />
Sony have unveiled a new product: the EQ Instant Messenger.<br />
The extra chat utility will allow you to access chat channels, guild channels and more without being logged into EQ.<br />
<br />
The service will have a trial period at first and then require a monthly fee to use<br />
<br />
<br />
You can read more on the EQIM here.<br />
<a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/eqim.jsp" target="_blank">http://eqlive.station.sony.com/eqim.jsp</a><br />
<br />
This was one of the features of Anarchy Online I really loved. You could access any chat channel and send tells from their website interface after logging on. I used to chat with folks in-game while at work. I think being able to access guildchat while at work would be great fun, but I cant tell if thats an option from looking at the pics.<br />
<br />
One thing it looks like it can do is let you search for those lost characters you have on other servers real fast. I know I have a level 27 ranger somewhere but I'm not about to search through 50+ server logons to find them.</td>
